<h2>Discretisation</h2>
<p>The motion of a falling object under gravity and air drag is described by:
                                                                $$\frac{dv}{dt} = g - \frac{k}{m}v^2$$
                                                                To simulate it numerically, we discretise time into small steps \(∆t\) and update the velocity as:                                                                                              $$v_{n+1} = v_n + \Delta t \left(g - \frac{k}{m}v_n^2\right)$$
								At terminal velocity, acceleration becomes zero:  
								So the update can also be written as:  
								$$v_{n+1} = v_n + \Delta t \cdot g \left(1 - \frac{v_n^2}{v_t^2}\right)$$                                                                                                                              </p>
